  <refnamediv>
    <refname>apple_mv</refname>

    <refpurpose>Do an apple move, moving metadata and the resource fork as well</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <para><emphasis remap="B">:BINDIR:/apple_mv<indexterm><primary>apple_mv</primary></indexterm></emphasis> <emphasis remap="I">SOURCE
    DEST</emphasis> <emphasis remap="B">:BINDIR:/apple_mv</emphasis> <emphasis
    remap="I">SOURCE</emphasis>... <emphasis remap="I">DIRECTORY</emphasis></para>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>

    <para><emphasis remap="B">apple_mv</emphasis> is a perl script to move
    SOURCE to DEST or multiple SOURCE(s) to DIRECTORY. It also moves the file 
    specific metadata (including resource forks) to the .AppleDouble directory
    for DEST or DIRECTORY. If the .AppleDouble directory doesn&#39;t exist for 
    DEST or DIRECTORY it will create it.</para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>EXAMPLES</title>

    <para><emphasis remap="B">:BINDIR:/apple_mv</emphasis> test.text
    /target/directory/</para>

    <para><emphasis remap="B">:BINDIR:/apple_mv</emphasis> test.text
    /target/directory/test2.text</para>

    <para><emphasis remap="B">:BINDIR:/apple_mv</emphasis> test.text
    testing.text /target/directory/</para>
  </refsect1>

